records.addlTxt:
Defendant Wendell Gregory Hamilton in court with attorney Calvin R Malone.  Thomas L. Potter appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant changes plea to GUILTY on both counts.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights. Plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  Court advised the defendant that as a convicted felon he may no longer use or possess any firearms; also he may not vote in any election until his civil rights have been restored.  Court further advised that if he is not a US citizen, deportation is possible.  

AS TO COUNT 1:
The Court sentenced defendant to serve 60 DAYS in the House of Corrections, with Huber release privileges for work, with good time credit.  
-Restitution set at $149.00 payable to Menards
-Defendant to pay Court costs and all applicable surcharges and assessments
-Defendant is to provide a DNA sample and pay the related surcharge 
-Defendant to pay restitution, Court costs, surcharges and assessments by payments of $100.00 per month commencing on June 1, 2016 and to continue on the first day of each month thereafter until paid in full; nonpayment penalty shall result in a civil judgment

AS TO COUNT 2:
The Court sentenced defendant to serve 60 DAYS in the House of Corrections, concurrent to COUNT 1,  with Huber release privileges for work, with good time credit.  
-Restitution set at $149.00 payable to Menards
-Defendant to pay Court costs and all applicable surcharges and assessments
-Defendant is to provide a DNA sample and pay the related surcharge 
-Defendant to pay restitution, Court costs, surcharges and assessments by payments of $100.00 per month commencing on June 1, 2016 and to continue on the first day of each month thereafter until paid in full; nonpayment penalty shall result in a civil judgment

Defendant to report to the House of Corrections on April 20, 2016 at 5:00 p.m.
